This paper discusses issues related to ethics and fairness in AI, with a focus on the impact of under-representation in computing fields on the design of algorithms and socio-technical systems. The paper draws connections between the lack of diversity in computing and biases encountered in datasets and machine learning models. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
